### EventChain API Examples
### Use these examples with REST clients like IntelliJ HTTP Client, VS Code REST Client, or Postman

### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### 1. Create a new event
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventType": "certificate",
  "metadata": "{\"name\":\"John Doe\",\"degree\":\"Bachelor of Science\",\"major\":\"Computer Science\",\"year\":\"2024\",\"institution\":\"University Example\"}"
}

### 2. Get all events
GET {{baseUrl}}/events

### 3. Get event by index
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/0

### 4. Verify event hash (replace with actual IPFS hash)
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/verify/QmXoypizjW3WknFiJnKLwHCnL72vedxjQkDDP1mXWo6uco

### 5. Create a document event
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventType": "document",
  "metadata": "{\"title\":\"Important Contract\",\"documentId\":\"DOC-2024-001\",\"version\":\"1.0\",\"status\":\"signed\"}"
}

### 6. Create a transaction event
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventType": "transaction",
  "metadata": "{\"transactionId\":\"TXN-12345\",\"amount\":1000,\"currency\":\"USD\",\"from\":\"Alice\",\"to\":\"Bob\",\"date\":\"2024-12-17\"}"
}

